             <div class="QA-item-header">What is the difference between an Executive Condominium (EC) and a Condominium?</div>
             <div class="QA-item-body">
               <div class="QA-item-body-content">Executive Condominiums (EC) are built by private developers, but are sold as public housing, whereas Condominiums are sold as private housing. This means that ECs are subject to government regulations such as a monthly household income eligibility cap, minimum occupational period of 5 years, and an MSR of 30%. Condominiums, on the other hand, are not subject to these regulations. Another difference is the leasehold, where ECs are only 99 year leaseholds and Condominiums can be 99 years, 999 years or freehold lease. Because of these regulations for ECs, they are also generally cheaper than Condominims in Singapore.</div>
             </div>
           </div>
   
