             <div class="QA-item-body">
               <div class="QA-item-body-content">3Gen flats, also known as Multi-Generational Flats, are are a relatively new type of HDB housing that has a larger flat space and allows for multi-generational families or large families to live together. They were introduced in 2013 and have flat sizes bigger than 5-room flats, and 2 bedrooms with attached bathrooms rather than the typical one bedroom with attached toilet found in 5-room flats and below. However, this type of flat does have additonal regulations from the government, such as the multi-generational family must have one married couple and their parents or one courting couple (fiancé and fiancée) and their parents co-living together. </div>
